DESCRIPTION:Hi advocates\,<br><br>Welcome to our joint LegList/Amigos calls
  every Tuesday from 12pm-1pm ET until election week in November.<br><br>Sha
 ring below the *<b>Zoom link</b>* for this call. This is a brand new link s
 pecific to these calls. <br><br><b>Join the Zoom Meeting:</b><br><a href="h
 ttps://theimmigrationhub.zoom.us/j/93022846161" target="_blank"><u>https://
 theimmigrationhub.zoom.us/j/93022846161</u></a><br><br>Meeting ID: 930 2284
  6161<br><br><br>Agenda items are always welcome.<b> Please send <a href="m
 ailto:joshua@theimmigrationhub.org" target="_blank">joshua@theimmigrationhu
 b.org</a> any agenda items by COB on Fridays.</b><br><b><br>Guidelines for 
 the Amigos Listserv &amp\; Calls</b><br>The Amigos network is a collaborati
 ve space created to facilitate information-sharing and activation of partne
 rs on timely immigration issues. We greatly value our partners in the Amigo
 s network and seek to foster a culture of trust\, equity\, and community. W
 ith this in mind\, we have implemented the guidelines outlined below to inf
 orm how we show up for ourselves and for each other. <br><br><b>The full ve
 rsion of the Amigos list guidelines can be found here: </b><a href="https:/
 /docs.google.com/document/d/1poTzhnjlpqJzdJ65VMkC9Lo091h08Ojj2fpYgkRN9-4/ed
 it?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><u><u><u>https://docs.google.com/document/d
 /1poTzhnjlpqJzdJ65VMkC9Lo091h08Ojj2fpYgkRN9-4/edit?usp=sharing</u></u></u><
 /a><br><br>Failure to abide by these guidelines may result in removal from 
 the Hub’s Amigos listserv and may also extend to other Hub listservs\, such
  as Leglist and Admin List/Table. Removal from the Amigos calls/listserv ca
 n be made at the discretion of Immigration Hub staff and may be done immedi
 ately\, without warning\, based on the offending action(s). <br><br><b>The 
 Amigos Network</b><br>The purpose of both the Amigos listserv and weekly Am
 igos calls is for organizations to share updates\, resources\, and actions 
 on federal immigration and refugee policy issues\; coordinate advocacy on f
 ederal legislation and executive policy\; and rapidly respond to national i
 mmigration and refugee policy developments.<br><br>At this time\, approxima
 tely 100 partners consistently join the weekly Amigos calls. A regularly-up
 dated list of Amigos partners can be viewed here: <br><br><a href="https://
 docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Q0A_LyzM_IYF9zV7WxwfICJOC53yBOj7LcHjVM8vNqA
 /edit#gid=0" target="_blank"><u><u><u>https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/
 d/1Q0A_LyzM_IYF9zV7WxwfICJOC53yBOj7LcHjVM8vNqA/edit#gid=0</u></u></u></a><b
 r><br>If you have any questions about the network\, or would like to add pe
 ople to the listserv\, please email: <a href="mailto:joshua@theimmigrationh
 ub.org">joshua@theimmigrationhub.org</a><br><b><u><br></u></b>Best\,<br><br
 >Josh\n\n-::~:~::~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:
 ~:~:~:~:~:~:~::~:~::-\nJoin Zoom Meeting\nhttps://theimmigrationhub.zoom.us
 /j/93022846161 (ID: 93022846161)\n\nJoin by phone\n(US) +1 888-475-4499\n\n
 Joining instructions: https://www.google.com/url?q=https://applications.zoo
 m.us/addon/invitation/detail?meetingUuid%3Df%252FPWEK1fRwivdAdNgFwqnA%253D%
 253D%26signature%3D0f628533b788b22cd5770fff783b2c9dfe1ea4412e846a8c78fa3f08
