DESCRIPTION:Hi advocates\,<br><br>Welcome to our Amigos calls every Tuesday
  from 12pm-1pm ET.<br><br>Sharing below the *<b>Zoom link</b>* for this cal
 l. This is a brand new link specific to these calls. <br><br><b>New Zoom Me
 eting Link for July 1 call only:</b><br><p dir="ltr"><a href="https://us02w
 eb.zoom.us/j/81473777256?pwd=g1JEqeN6THasLFBzgL5D0NDU62R1gM.1" target="_bla
 nk"><u><u>https://us02web.zoom.us/j/<u></u>81473777256?pwd=<u></u>g1JEqeN6T
 HasLFBzgL5D0NDU62R1gM<u></u>.1</u></u></a></p><p dir="ltr">Meeting ID: 814 
 7377 7256<br>Passcode: 563006</p><br>Agenda items are always welcome.<b> Pl
 ease send <a href="mailto:joshua@theimmigrationhub.org" target="_blank"><u>
 joshua@theimmigrationhub.org</u></a> any agenda items by COB on Fridays.</b
 ><br><b><br>Guidelines for the Amigos Listserv &amp\; Calls</b><br>The Amig
 os network is a collaborative space created to facilitate information-shari
 ng and activation of partners on timely immigration issues. We greatly valu
 e our partners in the Amigos network and seek to foster a culture of trust\
 , equity\, and community. With this in mind\, we have implemented the guide
 lines outlined below to inform how we show up for ourselves and for each ot
 her. <br><br><b>The full version of the Amigos list guidelines can be found
  here: </b><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1poTzhnjlpqJzdJ65VMk
 C9Lo091h08Ojj2fpYgkRN9-4/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>http
 s://docs.google.com/document/d/1poTzhnjlpqJzdJ65VMkC9Lo091h08Ojj2fpYgkRN9-4
 /edit?usp=sharing</u></u></u></u></a><br><br>Failure to abide by these guid
 elines may result in removal from the Hub’s Amigos listserv and may also ex
 tend to other Hub listservs\, such as Leglist and Admin List/Table. Removal
  from the Amigos calls/listserv can be made at the discretion of Immigratio
 n Hub staff and may be done immediately\, without warning\, based on the of
 fending action(s). <br><br><b>The Amigos Network</b><br>The purpose of both
  the Amigos listserv and weekly Amigos calls is for organizations to share 
 updates\, resources\, and actions on federal immigration and refugee policy
  issues\; coordinate advocacy on federal legislation and executive policy\;
  and rapidly respond to national immigration and refugee policy development
 s.<br><br>At this time\, approximately 100 partners consistently join the w
 eekly Amigos calls. A regularly-updated list of Amigos partners can be view
 ed here: <br><br><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Q0A_LyzM_
 IYF9zV7WxwfICJOC53yBOj7LcHjVM8vNqA/edit#gid=0" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>
 https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Q0A_LyzM_IYF9zV7WxwfICJOC53yBOj7LcH
 jVM8vNqA/edit#gid=0</u></u></u></u></a><br><br>If you have any questions ab
 out the network\, or would like to add people to the listserv\, please emai
 l: <a href="mailto:joshua@theimmigrationhub.org" target="_blank"><u>joshua@
 theimmigrationhub.org</u></a><br><b><u><br></u></b>Best\,<br><br>Josh
LAST-MODIFIED:20250809T145430Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Weekly Amigos Call
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
