DESCRIPTION:<p dir="ltr">We’re thrilled that you are joining us for this on
 line training! Here are some guidelines to help you make the most out of yo
 ur course.</p><p dir="ltr"><b>Technology</b> – We’ll be using <a href="http
 s://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/categories/200101697"><u>Zoom</u></a> for this
  training. We recommend you join from a computer with a high-speed internet
  connection to join the training for the best experience–we’ll be using an 
 online workbook and whiteboard\, and it is hard to toggle between these thr
 ee from a phone or tablet. You will have the option to join audio via compu
 ter or phone–if you choose the phone audio\, be sure to connect it to your 
 computer by dialing the participant ID number that zoom provides when you l
 og in. </p><p dir="ltr"><b>Join Zoom Meeting: </b><a href="https://us06web.
 zoom.us/j/87906840786?pwd=DCQLMPKdqOc9bc8QaW9Us9eA7THGBx.1">https://us06web
 .zoom.us/j/87906840786?pwd=DCQLMPKdqOc9bc8QaW9Us9eA7THGBx.1</a><br><br><b>M
 eeting ID: </b>879 0684 0786<br><b><u>Passcode: 141170</u></b><br><br>One t
 ap mobile<br>+13017158592\,\,87906840786# US (Washington DC)<br>+1305224196
 8\,\,87906840786# US<br><br>Dial by your location<br>• +1 301 715 8592 US (
 Washington DC)<br>• +1 305 224 1968 US<br>• +1 309 205 3325 US<br>• +1 312 
 626 6799 US (Chicago)<br>• +1 646 931 3860 US<br>• +1 929 205 6099 US (New 
 York)<br>• +1 507 473 4847 US<br>• +1 564 217 2000 US<br>• +1 669 444 9171 
 US<br>• +1 669 900 6833 US (San Jose)<br>• +1 689 278 1000 US<br>• +1 719 3
 59 4580 US<br>• +1 253 205 0468 US<br>• +1 253 215 8782 US (Tacoma)<br>• +1
  346 248 7799 US (Houston)<br>• +1 360 209 5623 US<br>• +1 386 347 5053 US<
 br>• 877 853 5257 US Toll-free<br>• 888 475 4499 US Toll-free<br>• 833 548 
 0276 US Toll-free<br>• 833 548 0282 US Toll-free<br>• 833 928 4608 US Toll-
 free<br>• 833 928 4609 US Toll-free<br>• 833 928 4610 US Toll-free<br><br>M
 eeting ID: 879 0684 0786<br><br>Find your local number: <a href="https://us
 06web.zoom.us/u/kVvCYD2wq">https://us06web.zoom.us/u/kVvCYD2wq</a></p><p di
 r="ltr"><b>Learning &amp\; Engagement</b> – In the training\, we’ll build a
  community of learning through trainer instruction\, activities\, small gro
 up breakouts\, and large group discussion. We’d love to see you on video! W
 hether you turn on your video or not\, we invite you to unplug from your ot
 her work and focus on the training by putting up an out-of-office message a
 nd silencing notifications. We’ll make sure there is time for breaks and sp
 ace for individual reflection. </p><p dir="ltr"><b>Training Materials </b>–
  We’ll workshop real-world scenarios together using a workbook developed fo
 r this training\, which we’ll share before the session. Please print it out
  or have it open on your screen and ready to use for the training. </p>
